 book to provide a comparative overview of the major ethnic return groups in Europe and East Asia, reveals how the sociocultural characteristics and national origins of the migrants influence their levels of marginalization in their ethnic homelands, forcing many of them to redefine the meanings of home and homeland.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aEmigration and immigrationvCross-cultural studies. 0aEmigration and immigrationxCross-cultural studies. 0aReturn migrationvCross-cultural studies. 0aReturn migrationxCross-cultural studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh1 aTsuda, Takeyuki, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477206840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804772068423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804772068.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles